neyman's walking stick is a great aggro weapon. It is 9/24 and procs tashania. Enchanters all over will tell you about the aggro of the spell. Weapon is not to slow and can put out ok damage, but if you are being counted on as the damage dealer then use it till it procs then switch it out.<br><br>Besides that train the people you raid/group with not to overaggro and to turn their attack off when they do in a bad situation.<br><br><br>Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umenaden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menaden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/17/02 5:37:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Warriors....</span><hr size=1> All is in agro control ... i'm a SK and i've mostly play with a monk and that was the monk that was tanking ... <br><br>To avoid taking too much agro i was fighing as max melee limits, avoiding using AC debuff (max taunt with those) and only dark when mob was at 50% or less hp.<br><br>With that i never really had some pb and if i wanted to overtaunt i only had to cast 2 spells (shadow vortex - shroud of pain ..both ACdebuff) or HT ... i was sure to get agro in 99% of the case ... <br><br>And if really too much agro ...well FD is usefull to help your MT build his agro up again. <p><br><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=128257">Menaden</a></b><br><b><a href="http://firionavie.org/reso/">Resolution</a></b> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxethux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xethux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tyrannical ru